The paper deals with source coding and compression of correlated Gaussian random variables, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of geometric approaches and algorithms, which are common in machine learning and computer vision (cs.MM). The paper discusses the lossy compression of network data, which falls under the category of signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). The paper also involves the calculation of rates and distortion measures, which are common in statistical learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the applicability of the methods to other problems in multi-user communication, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
